The combined dataset (28 S + TEF 1
+ RPB2 ) of Aureoboletus included 202 taxa with 2253 nucleotide sites, and the alignment was deposited in TreeBASE ( S 28834
). Tree topologies generated by BI and ML analyses were identical, albeit there were slight differences in statistical support for some relationships.
shows a branch-length phylogram inferred with RAxML with support values. Molecular phylogenetic analyses revealed that the new collections from China were grouped into three independent lineages (1, 2, and 3) (
). Lineage 1, which has strong statistical support (BS = 99%, PP = 1.0), included three specimens ( FHMU 4688, FHMU 4695, and FHMU 4722) from southern China ; in lineage 2, three collections ( FHMU 2766, FHMU 6509, and FHMU 6510) from southwestern China were grouped together with high statistical support (BS = 100%, PP = 1.0); in lineage 3, one specimen ( FHMU 3797) from southern China and two collections ( FHMU 864 and FHMU 6511) from southeastern China were grouped together with high statistical support (BS = 94%, PP = 0.98).

